the command is not properin the image here is the real one:

strings /path/to/extracted/apk/assets/flutter_assets/kernel_blob.bin > extracted_code.dart
Sometimes, It's a roller coaster ride after you hit `flutter run` https://t.co/mVZ7xFvfQH

Now you'll be get one dart file which won't be cleaned you need to find the keywords like main, runApp, MateralApp, or your own code if you remember.

it will give you the file path and file content. now you have to create the new flutter project and set it up manually. https://t.co/2n5gy89cXV

Use `apktool` in order to extract the components of the apk file. basically .apk file is a zip and you can extract it.

Flutter keeps the source code in the file `kernel_blob.bin`

using the following command should help you extract the code into a dart file: https://t.co/2jY8q92p83

How to get stars on your GitHub repo?

Easy! people like what they see, you have to write a good README .md file to show the value of the repo.
